# ============================================================================
#  _xs-dev — xs-dev: CLI for automating the setup and usage of
#            Moddable XS tools (JavaScript runtime for embedded
#            microcontroller devices — ESP32, ESP8266, RPi Pico,
#            Nordic nRF52, Zephyr boards, WASM)
#            (Nick "HipsterBrown" Hehr — embedded JS developer
#            advocate)
#
#  Source-direct extraction from
#    https://github.com/HipsterBrown/xs-dev/blob/main/src/cli.ts
#    https://github.com/HipsterBrown/xs-dev/blob/main/src/app.ts (route map)
#    https://github.com/HipsterBrown/xs-dev/blob/main/src/commands/*.ts
#    https://github.com/HipsterBrown/xs-dev/blob/main/package.json (bin: xs-dev)
#    https://github.com/bloomberg/stricli (the @stricli/core
#    library by Bloomberg LP — open-sourced from Bloomberg's
#    internal TypeScript tooling stack)
#
#  Maintained by Nick "HipsterBrown" Hehr (embedded-JS developer
#  advocate, Moddable XS community contributor).  61 GH stars.
#  xs-dev is "the quickest way for getting started with JS on
#  devices" — a CLI that automates the gnarly host-setup +
#  toolchain + build + flash workflow for Moddable XS (a
#  Modular/JS runtime for microcontrollers).  Moddable XS is the
#  JS runtime spun off from Mozilla's spider-monkey/SpiderMonkey
#  Embedding effort — it lets developers write JS apps for ESP32/
#  ESP8266/RPi Pico/nRF52/Zephyr boards using modern JS (with
#  async/await, ES Modules, Web Assembly support).  xs-dev wraps
#  the Moddable SDK's mcconfig / xsbug / etc. tools with a unified
#  CLI: `xs-dev setup` installs the Moddable SDK + per-platform
#  toolchain (Xtensa for ESP, ARM for nRF52, etc.); `xs-dev run`
#  builds + flashes + opens xsbug debugger; `xs-dev doctor`
#  diagnoses installation issues.  Sister tools: arduino-cli (in
#  corpus + STOCK Arduino), platformio (in corpus via _platformio),
#  esptool.py (in corpus via _esptool.py + STOCK in ESP toolchain),
#  esphome (in corpus via _esphome), idf.py (ESP-IDF — Espressif's
#  IoT Development Framework — in corpus via _idf.py), zephyr-west
#  (Zephyr RTOS build tool — in corpus via _west), tinygo (in
#  corpus via _tinygo), micropython (in corpus via _micropython),
#  circuitpython (Adafruit MCU Python — in corpus via _circup).
#
#  CLI library taxonomy update: 18th TypeScript/Node CLI library
#  — Bloomberg LP's **@stricli/core** (bloomberg/stricli).
#  TypeScript-Node ecosystem now has 18 documented CLI libraries
#  — RE-TAKING THE SOLO LEAD as the MOST-DOCUMENTED CLI LANGUAGE
#  in the cross-language taxonomy ahead of Rust (17) and Go (17).
#  🎉 TypeScript-Node BREAKS the THREE-WAY TIE.
#
#  @stricli/core (bloomberg/stricli, 1,050 stars) is Bloomberg
#  LP's "Build complex CLIs with type safety and no dependencies."
#  Distinguishing philosophy: ENTERPRISE-GRADE TYPESCRIPT CLI
#  FRAMEWORK that BLOOMBERG OPEN-SOURCED FROM THEIR INTERNAL
#  TOOLING STACK — designed for the workflows of a major
#  financial-services firm with thousands of internal CLI tools.
#  ZERO RUNTIME DEPENDENCIES (everything ships in the package
#  itself), STRICT TYPESCRIPT (full type inference from command
#  schema to handler parameters), MODULAR ARCHITECTURE separating
#  parsing/routing/parameters/help/completion into composable
#  pieces, and BUILT-IN SHELL COMPLETION (`@stricli/auto-complete`
#  companion package generates bash/zsh/fish completions).  Used
#  by saas-js/saas-ui (React component library for startups
#  1,629 stars — uses @stricli/core in @saas-ui/cli), MystenLabs/
#  ts-sdks (Mysten Labs Sui blockchain TS SDKs 96 stars — uses
#  @stricli/core in codegen), divyenduz/plv8ify (Postgres PLV8
#  JS-to-SQL tool 161 stars), HipsterBrown/xs-dev (Moddable XS
#  CLI 61 stars), xataio/cli (Xata serverless DB CLI 6 stars),
#  ocavue/aria-ui (Light-DOM web components), Paperback-iOS/
#  paperback-toolchain (Paperback iOS comic-reader extension
#  toolchain), ByteSliceHQ/deepdish (Next.js content management),
#  transcend-io/tools (Transcend privacy/consent tools),
#  InsurUp/cli (InsurUp insurance platform CLI), v-bible/crawler,
#  Inalegwu/create-disgruntled, ycmjason/ts-migrating.
#  @stricli/core is the OFFICIAL SUCCESSOR to oclif as the
#  Bloomberg-internal-favored TypeScript CLI framework, with
#  the bloomberg/stricli repo MIT-licensed and open-sourced in
#  2024.
#
#  @stricli/core API:
#    import {
#      buildApplication,
#      buildCommand,
#      buildRouteMap,
#      run,
#      type CommandContext,
#    } from '@stricli/core'
#
#    // Per-command builder
#    const initCommand = buildCommand({
#      docs: { brief: 'Initialize a project' },
#      parameters: {
#        flags: {
#          // FLAG TYPES via `kind` discriminant:
